				 Railway safety tips by SMS
 A STAFF REPORTER																								South Eastern Railway has tied up with BSNL to make people aware of the right way to manoeuvre level crossings. BSNL cellphone subscribers have been receiving text messages on safety tips.																								A railway official said vehicles are often hit by trains at unmanned level crossings. 																								Drivers usually do not check whether a train is approaching before driving through a level crossing. This often results in mishaps for both the train and the vehicle, said an official.																								The two-month campaign started on November 13 and will cover around 30 lakh subscribers.
